Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @Potatoes{3} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @Oil{to taste}, season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @Tomato{1}.

Mix @Water{2%tbsp}, @Salt{1/4%tsp} and @Breadcrumbs{1%pack} with the @Irish Beef Mince{250%g} in a large #bowl{}.

Season with @Pepper{to taste}.

Mix together by hand until everything is combined.

Shape into burgers about 2cm thick, 1 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}.

Fry the burgers until browned and cooked through, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Turn every ~{3-4%minutes}, lowering heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: Beef is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove pan from heat. Place a round of @Goat's Cheese{100%g} on top of each burger.

Cover and set aside until cheese is melted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Not a fan of goat's cheese? Don't worry, these burgers will still be delicious without!

Just before the wedges are finished cooking, pop the @Brioche Buns{2} into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, spread some @Mayo{2%sachets} over each bun base.

Add the burger, a drizzle of @Sweet Chilli Sauce{1%sachet} and sliced tomato.

Sandwich closed with the bun lid.

Serve with the potato wedges alongside.